<subSubSection id="2DCC75DAAC65FFBBFF75F8F885707C0F" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" type="description">
<paragraph id="65692651AC65FFB6FF75F8F887A47AF3" blockId="5.[136,1452,1694,2081]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC65FFB6FF75F8F8852E7A2B" bold="true" box="[189,337,1838,1864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">Description:</emphasis>
—On CMD after 72 h, colony diameter 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC65FFB6FCDDF8F887F17A2A" box="[789,910,1838,1865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="21.0">21–25 mm</quantity>
at 25 °C, and 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC65FFB6FBF8F8F880D67A2A" box="[1072,1193,1838,1865]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="28.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="20.0">20–37 mm</quantity>
at 30 °C. After 7 days, mycelium loose, a layer of aerial mycelium covering the entire plate at 25 °C and 30 °C (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC65FFB6FB5CF884812B7A0F" box="[1172,1364,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,786,1558]" captionTargetId="figure-194@5.[183,1404,779,1565]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichoderma bombaxalis (CGMCC 3.20851). Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days (A. on PDA, B. on SNA, C. on CMD). Cultures at 30 °C after 7 days (E. on PDA, F. on SNA, G. on CMD). D, H, I, J. Conidia and phialides. K, L. Conidia. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571423/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">FIGURE. 2C, G</figureCitation>
). Many conidiophores formed by 5 days, unknown aromatic odour, and no pigment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65692651AC65FFB6FF40F84C85877543" blockId="5.[136,1452,1694,2081]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">
On PDA after 72 h, colony diameter 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC65FFB6FDD4F84C86077AD6" box="[540,632,1946,1973]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
at 25 °C, and 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC65FFB6FCDBF84C870F7AD6" box="[787,880,1946,1973]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
at 30 °C. At 25 °C, white colony, cotton-like, dense hyphae. At 30 ℃, white flocculent colony, uniform mycelial density, coconut aroma, and no pigment. After 7 days, colony diameter 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC65FFB6FE8EF83485BF7A9E" box="[326,448,2018,2045]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 mm</quantity>
at 25 °C (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC65FFB6FDFDF83486B77A9F" box="[565,712,2018,2044]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,786,1558]" captionTargetId="figure-194@5.[183,1404,779,1565]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichoderma bombaxalis (CGMCC 3.20851). Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days (A. on PDA, B. on SNA, C. on CMD). Cultures at 30 °C after 7 days (E. on PDA, F. on SNA, G. on CMD). D, H, I, J. Conidia and phialides. K, L. Conidia. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571423/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">FIGURE 2A</figureCitation>
), and 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC65FFB6FCC4F83487077A9E" box="[780,888,2018,2045]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10 mm</quantity>
at 30 °C, not producing concentric rings or radial rays of mycelium (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC65FFB6FE94F7D085937543" box="[348,492,2054,2080]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,786,1558]" captionTargetId="figure-194@5.[183,1404,779,1565]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichoderma bombaxalis (CGMCC 3.20851). Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days (A. on PDA, B. on SNA, C. on CMD). Cultures at 30 °C after 7 days (E. on PDA, F. on SNA, G. on CMD). D, H, I, J. Conidia and phialides. K, L. Conidia. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571423/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">FIGURE 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="31A976D9AC66FFB5FF40FA02813A7B6D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571425" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6571425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571425/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="153" startId="6.[136,229,1492,1514]" targetBox="[167,1423,206,1448]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="65692651AC66FFB5FF40FA02813A7B6D" blockId="6.[136,1452,1492,1550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC66FFB5FF40FA028482788A" bold="true" box="[136,253,1492,1514]" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
A. Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days on xylan medium. B. Following Congo red dyeing and decolorization on xylan medium. C. Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days on CMC-Na medium. D. Following Congo red dyeing and decolorization on CMC-Na medium.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="65692651AC66FFB5FF75F9EB866F7A4C" blockId="6.[136,1452,1597,2019]" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">
On SNA after 72 h, colony diameter 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC66FFB5FDBAF9EB86907B34" box="[626,751,1597,1624]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="15.0">15–22 mm</quantity>
at 25 °C, and 
<quantity id="A22E8BB4AC66FFB5FC55F9EB80697B34" box="[925,1046,1597,1623]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="153" unit="mm" value="19.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="17.0">17–21 mm</quantity>
at 30 °C. White colony, mycelium loose, light coconut aroma. After 7 days, colony edge was irregular, and mycelium was loose, coconut aroma and no pigment (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC66FFB5FF39F95385E07BFC" box="[241,415,1669,1695]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,786,1558]" captionTargetId="figure-194@5.[183,1404,779,1565]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichoderma bombaxalis (CGMCC 3.20851). Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days (A. on PDA, B. on SNA, C. on CMD). Cultures at 30 °C after 7 days (E. on PDA, F. on SNA, G. on CMD). D, H, I, J. Conidia and phialides. K, L. Conidia. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571423/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">FIGURE 2B, F</figureCitation>
). Conidial production noted after 5 days. Conidiophores branched verticillium-like, phialides subulate, variable in length, in whorls or opposite, 2–3(–4) branches, (8.8–)11–18(–23.2) × (1.3–)2.0–3.0(–3.4) μm (
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC66FFB5FF5DF91C84DC7B82" box="[149,163,1738,1761]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">x</emphasis>
= 14.3 × 2.4 μm, n = 20) (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC66FFB5FE06F91B86CE7B84" box="[462,689,1741,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,786,1558]" captionTargetId="figure-194@5.[183,1404,779,1565]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichoderma bombaxalis (CGMCC 3.20851). Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days (A. on PDA, B. on SNA, C. on CMD). Cultures at 30 °C after 7 days (E. on PDA, F. on SNA, G. on CMD). D, H, I, J. Conidia and phialides. K, L. Conidia. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571423/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">FIGURE 2D, H, I, J</figureCitation>
). Conidia obovate to ellipsoidal, roughened (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC66FFB5FB64F91B81227B84" box="[1196,1373,1741,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1590,1612]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,786,1558]" captionTargetId="figure-194@5.[183,1404,779,1565]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Trichoderma bombaxalis (CGMCC 3.20851). Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days (A. on PDA, B. on SNA, C. on CMD). Cultures at 30 °C after 7 days (E. on PDA, F. on SNA, G. on CMD). D, H, I, J. Conidia and phialides. K, L. Conidia. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571423/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">FIGURE 2K, L</figureCitation>
), (2.0–)2.5–3.6(–4.5) × (1.0–)1.4–2.0(–2.4) µm (
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC66FFB5FDABF93886F47A68" box="[611,651,1774,1803]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">x =</emphasis>
3.1 × 1.7 µm, n = 50), length/width ratio (1.2–)1.5–1.8 (–2.4) (
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC66FFB5FA9EF938811B7A66" box="[1366,1380,1774,1797]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="153">x</emphasis>
= 1.6, n = 50). No sexual morphogenesis.
</paragraph>
