<td id="98374D6FAC67004CF925FC108C777946" box="[1773,2056,966,1061]" gridcol="6" gridrow="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Irregularly branched, usually verticillium-like</td>
</tr>
<tr id="DBE62413AC67004CFF58FB8C8C7779BE" box="[144,2056,1114,1245]" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">
<th id="98374D6FAC67004CFF58FB8C856279BE" box="[144,285,1114,1245]" gridcol="0" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Phialides</th>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFEF2FB8C863879BE" box="[314,583,1114,1245]" gridcol="1" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Solitary or alternating in pairs, subulate or lageniform, (9–)15–30(–46) × (2.3–)3.0–3.5(–4.0) μm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFD91FB8C870F79BE" box="[601,880,1114,1245]" gridcol="2" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">In whorls or opposite, generally 2–3(–4) branches, subulate, (8.8–)11–18(–23.2) × (1.3–)2.0–3.0(–3.4) μm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFC4CFB8C80E579BE" box="[900,1178,1114,1245]" gridcol="3" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">In whorls or opposite, generally 2–3 branches, subulate, (4.1–)8–16(–23.2) × (1.5–)2.3–3.1(–5.6) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFB65FB8C81C879BE" box="[1197,1463,1114,1245]" gridcol="4" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">In whorls of 2–4, solitary, or alternating in pairs, subulate, (15.7–)22–30(– 46) × (2.9–)3–3.7(–4.2) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFA03FB8C82AC79BE" box="[1483,1747,1114,1245]" gridcol="5" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">In whorls of 2–4, solitary or alternating in pairs, subulate, (8–)17–32(–45) × (2.4–)3–4(–4.8) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CF925FB8C8C7779BE" box="[1773,2056,1114,1245]" gridcol="6" gridrow="4" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Solitary or alternating in pairs, subulate, (3.8–)18–36 (–57) × (2.6–)3.1–3.9(–4.4) µm</td>
</tr>
<tr id="DBE62413AC67004CFF58FAC58C7778D9" box="[144,2056,1299,1466]" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">
<th id="98374D6FAC67004CFF58FAC5856278D9" box="[144,285,1299,1466]" gridcol="0" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Conidia</th>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFEF2FAC5863878D9" box="[314,583,1299,1466]" gridcol="1" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hyaline, subcylindrical, often ellipsoidal, (3.7–)4.7– 10(–18) × (2.3–)3.0–4.0(– 5.5) μm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFD91FAC5870F78D9" box="[601,880,1299,1466]" gridcol="2" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hyaline, obovate to subcylindrical, often ellipsoidal, (2.0–)2.5–3.6(– 4.5) × (1.0–)1.4–2.0(–2.4) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFC4CFAC580E578D9" box="[900,1178,1299,1466]" gridcol="3" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hyaline, typically subglobose, but sometimes subellipsoidal, (2.4–)3.3– 4.2(–10) × (2.0–)2.5–3.1(–6) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFB65FAC581C878D9" box="[1197,1463,1299,1466]" gridcol="4" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hyaline, ellipsoidal to subcylindrical, (5.9–)6.4– 10.4(–13.5) × (2.7–)3.2– 4.3(–4.7) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CFA03FAC582AC78D9" box="[1483,1747,1299,1466]" gridcol="5" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hyaline, obovate to subcylindrical, often ellipsoidal, (3.9–)5.6–9.0(– 12.6) × (3.0–)3.3–4.3(–6.6) µm</td>
<td id="98374D6FAC67004CF925FAC58C7778D9" box="[1773,2056,1299,1466]" gridcol="6" gridrow="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="154">Hyaline, obovate to elongate-obovate or subellipsoidal, (4.5–)5.9–9.3(–12.0) × (2.8–)3.2–4.2(–5.2) µm</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65692651AC68FFBBFF40FF4886F07DDB" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,364]" box="[136,655,158,184]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC68FFBBFF40FF4886F07DDB" box="[136,655,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Ability to degrade cellulose and hemicellulose</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65692651AC68FFBBFF40FF1485707C0F" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName id="A2D65DD2AC68FFBBFF40FF1485DF7DBF" authorityName="Jing Z. Sun &amp; H. W. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,416,194,220]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Trichoderma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bombaxalis">
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC68FFBBFF40FF1485DF7DBF" box="[136,416,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Trichoderma bombaxalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was inoculated on xylan medium and CMC-Na medium for 7 days (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC68FFBBFB5DFF14816C7DBF" box="[1173,1299,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1492,1514]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,206,1448]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,190,1468]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days on xylan medium. B. Following Congo red dyeing and decolorization on xylan medium. C. Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days on CMC-Na medium. D. Following Congo red dyeing and decolorization on CMC-Na medium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571425/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">FIGURE 3</figureCitation>
). Transparent zones were present around the colony on CMC-Na medium following 
<collectingCountry id="1DC166C1AC68FFBBFC55FF3087977C63" box="[925,1000,230,256]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Congo</collectingCountry>
red dyeing and decolouration (
<figureCitation id="FDED3AD4AC68FFBBFA8CFF3084D27C47" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[136,229,1492,1514]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,206,1448]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,190,1468]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days on xylan medium. B. Following Congo red dyeing and decolorization on xylan medium. C. Cultures at 25 °C after 7 days on CMC-Na medium. D. Following Congo red dyeing and decolorization on CMC-Na medium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571425/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">FIGURE 3D</figureCitation>
), indicating a capacity to hydrolyze cellulose. However, no transparent zones were observed on the xylan medium, indicating weak or no ability to use 
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC68FFBBFDDEFEF887A97C2B" box="[534,982,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
hemicellulose. 
<taxonomicName id="A2D65DD2AC68FFBBFD76FEF887A97C2B" authorityName="Jing Z. Sun &amp; H. W. Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[702,982,302,328]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Trichoderma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bombaxalis">Trichoderma bombaxalis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
may be a potential candidate for 
<emphasis id="57A2FA43AC68FFBBFA80FEF881D37C2B" box="[1352,1452,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">cellulase</emphasis>
exploration.
</paragraph>
